    <h1>CHRISTINA WINSLØW</h1>
    
<p>In my art, I focus on conveying all the universal facets of life. I challenge conventional materials with my working methods, often blending delicate drawn expressions with paint and spray. Thus, the works exude an atmosphere of dreamy infinity. An aesthetic union and a very special sensuality.

I think a lot about sustainability in connection with my art, including through my choice of materials. I create my art using materials that already exist, and materials I find in nature and places I visit, such as recycling centers. My approach to work is very intuitive; I take many photos and write notes that inspire me and which I use when creating art.</p>
   
